		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The C64 and NES CPUs are practically identical (6502 NMOS version), so you've had a start.
<br />
<br />I used this one a lot when I was starting out:
<br /><a href="http://www.geocities.com/oneelkruns/asm1step.html" class="postlink">http://www.geocities.com/oneelkruns/asm1step.html</a>
<br />
<br />If you can find someone's demo/game source code and make it assemble with whatever assembler they used, that can be an example to start with.

		

